  "methodology_note": "Adoption rate = deployment-positive companies / (deployment + strategic) × 100. Strong-term search ('generative AI' or 'large language model') is run across all 10-K (or 20-F) filings in the window; results are matched by CIK. Companies with a valid CIK not found in strong-term results are classified as 'strategic' (AI mentioned broadly). Unknown = CIK mismatch or API blocked. US sample: ~25 major S&P 500 companies. China sample: ~20 major Chinese ADRs (SEC filers only — not Tencent, ByteDance). China sample is tech-sector-heavy; compare directionally."
